Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the commotion \Nthat Lotte and Luise inadvertently caused,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.46,0:00:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,dad's grand concert \Nwas reduced to shambles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.52,0:00:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the wake of that, mom is seriously considering \Nmarrying for the second time, possibly her boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.14,0:00:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as they had escaped one quandary, \Nyet another, bigger problem is on their hands already. {to have (problems, debts, etc.); to take on (a responsibility); to be burdened with (e.g. care of a family member); to have (children, etc.) to provide for}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.09,0:00:28.18,Sign,,0,0,120,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 18 \N {\fs35} Dad and Mom Meet Again {お父さんとお母さんの再会} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.01,0:00:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if mom really set her mind on marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.02,0:00:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,One would think, \N"Well, Herr Editor is a good man."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.66,0:00:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I quite like him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.18,0:00:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have a dad of our own!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.83,0:00:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need anyone else but our dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.06,0:00:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cold tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.10,0:00:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.67,0:01:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, mom can really \Nmarry her Editor-in-chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.35,0:01:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be something we can do \Nto make dad and mom start getting along again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.05,0:01:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, what {\i1}can{\i0} we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.44,0:01:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That - I'd like to know myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.32,0:01:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, it seems, ever since they day they parted, \Nthey haven't talked to each other, not once! {this is bad!}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.04,0:01:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If they would have at least talked today...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.07,0:01:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! We {\i1}make{\i0} them talk, instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.38,0:01:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You think they can reconcile, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.26,0:01:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come one, we gotta try, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take it in our own hands \Nand make dad and mom meet when they least expect!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please make it work this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.21,0:02:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I overslept beyond possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.01,0:02:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.82,0:02:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you even try to wake me up sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning. \NBut you came home so late last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.13,0:02:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You looked like you need plenty of rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.40,0:02:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Thanks, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I wasn't too much of a nuisance \Nto Editor last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.64,0:02:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He had to spend an entire evening \Nlistening to my endless quibbling. {for a long time; at (great) length; lengthily; long-windedly; tediously}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.08,0:02:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd never tell he can actually be that attentive, too. {despite appearances}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.95,0:02:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you love him, after all? Our Herr Editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... A letter had come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.29,0:02:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,From who?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.19,0:02:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That, I don't know. But this morning, \NI found it slipped into under our door. {entrance; front door; entryway; entranceway; entry hall; vestibule; porch; foyer; mud room}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's lunch together today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.26,0:03:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting at Don Giovanni restaurant at two o'clock?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.67,0:03:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would make such a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.94,0:03:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But it shouldn't be a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.84,0:03:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably, some terrific person sent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he knows Don Giovanni \Nis mom's stamping ground! {regular; usual; favourite; favorite; preferred; accustomed}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.01,0:03:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.72,0:03:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please-please, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.49,0:03:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to Don Giovanni today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.23,0:03:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.15,0:03:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Luise? Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.34,0:03:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't feel well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.95,0:03:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My last night's concert \Nwas turned into a trainwreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.01,0:03:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As you'd expect, my head \Nis still quite heavy this morning. {fresh; refreshing; invigorating; pleasant; delightful morning}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.09,0:03:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter had arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,From who?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.55,0:04:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't know. There's no return address.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"I wish to have a lunch with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At two o'clock, come to Don Giovanni's.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.62,0:04:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting for you at the third table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I still wish to surprise you, \Nso I shall keep my name a secret..?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.42,0:04:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.34,0:04:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd need to come up with a better ruse to trick me. {unsure, lit is "this way won't do to to hook; to catch; to trap; to ensnare me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.73,0:04:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as of now, it's as plain as the nose on your face,\Njust who would such a thing. {unobstructed view; perspective; visibility; vista/forecast; outlook; prospect; prediction}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.93,0:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Irene Gerlach's prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.27,0:04:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By appearing in Munich when I least expect, \Nshe plans to catch me completely by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.25,0:04:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds just like something she'd do. {/this is so selfish, just like her}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, either way, you'll go there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My, oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.85,0:05:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't sound like she's giving me a choice. {not sure what he means: How can I not go?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.06,0:05:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My, oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.90,0:05:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.16,0:05:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm off, Lotte. \NI hope I'm not getting lectured for coming this late. {lit: if you don't hurry, you'll be late too - no fucking clue what she means since we've seen them woke up late today, so she is obviously late for school already, so I must assume lotte doesn't go to school today, like, it was jueves on the day of mini-concert, it was friday on the next day when they switched places back, in the evening of friday it was a big concert, it's saturday now, but we'll see if it's just some "later than late" kind of deal when lotte is still supposed to go to school today, or the scriptwriters were dumb and didn't pay attention, or they are actually wrong and it's mom woh is mixing things up or something due to fatigue, like maybe she just says this on autopilot, without thinking, like all moms do}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.77,0:05:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom... Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.94,0:05:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This was in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.83,0:05:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Editor must have forgotten it last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's so careless sometimes! \NI'll be sure to return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Which reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.62,0:05:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The man who wrote that letter -\Nyou know him quite well, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? No! I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then. Tell him I'll be there, \Nat Don Giovanni's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.30,0:05:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to meeting whoever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:05:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.91,0:05:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At two, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.34,0:06:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure. The third table, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.68,0:06:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'm gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.63,0:06:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Was I too rash? {not sure if it's hayamatta - "I did something rash/premature" or ayamatta "I was wrong/made a mistake/should apologize"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.53,0:06:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Then, Editor, have you ever considered \Ngetting married yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Most naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.30,0:06:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea. \NWho could she be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, Miss Körner, \Nthat could be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.45,0:06:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you ever think about entering a marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.38,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm dreading the moment \Nwhen I have to see Miss Körner today. {/today, what face will I make before ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.14,0:07:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,An article about Herr Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Need to cover last night's concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard about it, too. \NThe way it got ruined was a sight to behold... {rare; extraordinary; singular big failure/mistake}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.34,0:07:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. To see the concert destroyed so spectacularly \Nis a once-in-a-lifetime experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.85,0:07:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that'll serve to bring him \Ndown a peg or two. {lit: maybe it was a good medicine to a conceit; vanity; pride; self-importance; egotism man}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.29,0:07:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, good morning, \Nmuch obliged for the yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.20,0:07:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.36,0:07:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Forgot something, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.51,0:07:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.81,0:07:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We might need to discuss something... {/I want to talk to you}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.78,0:07:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.81,0:07:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not quite... \NHow about we meet for a lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.07,0:08:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.93,0:08:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sounds delightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.03,0:08:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I will gladly join you at Don Giovanni's, at two today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.93,0:08:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At two, at Don Giovanni's?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.30,0:08:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Third table, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember! {/roger that}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.31,0:08:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Third table, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He came. Dad's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.38,0:08:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, everything is according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.85,0:08:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost two o'clock. \NJust need to wait for mom. {/only mom remains}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.40,0:08:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hold back, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.94,0:08:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it a lamb, or a veal, \Nanything you like - I'll get it for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.08,0:08:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And for dessert, you can get \Nas much plum pudding as you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Super!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two are here, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Screwed! {/the worst}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.26,0:09:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A reservation for the third table...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.70,0:09:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We were waiting for you. \NThis way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.93,0:09:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.97,0:09:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Isn't that the guy who was swinging the stick \Nat the last night's concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.16,0:09:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Something like Rudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.23,0:09:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Ludwig Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.73,0:09:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That dope Palfy. {idiot; fool; dope}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.89,0:09:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He has the nerve to show up here \Nafter bungling a concert so miserably!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.23,0:09:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a hint of shame! {/he is carefree}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't tolerate that slander!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.98,0:09:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone is waiting for me at the third table.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.30,0:09:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.88,0:09:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.26,0:09:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, your table is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.25,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it... Herr Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.92,0:10:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I know you from somewhere? {actually says "you know my name" but he obv does so what's the point asking?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I don't recognize your face. \NDid someone invite you to wait at this table as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.97,0:10:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.02,0:10:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At this third table.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.49,0:10:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How peculiar...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.92,0:10:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in the world might be behind this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.09,0:10:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, boy! Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't mix things up at some point, did we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.13,0:10:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.73,0:10:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're in trouble now. \NMom is also coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.70,0:10:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be someone special to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.70,0:10:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman you're waiting for. {/the other party you're waiting for}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.67,0:11:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.34,0:11:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have given her some trouble last night, \Nso I'm apologizing with a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.82,0:11:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd wager, she is very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.68,0:11:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you intend to marry her, too? {/serious about}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.15,0:11:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not... \NWe still have a rather long way to go. {/it's complicated}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.94,0:11:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take a clairvoyant to know - \Nyou're poised to propose to someone. {hopefully by "to catch sight of; to see; to suppose; to assume from appearances" he means "as soon as I saw you, I knew you're making a proposal today"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.11,0:11:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, marriage sure is a nice thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.26,0:11:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, if your beloved one is just as honest a person \Nas you are, you'll be certain to have a happy marriage. {lit: when loved by a sincere; honest; faithful man like you, this woman will certainly become happy}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.03,0:11:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.77,0:11:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why... {actually anata, which is you, but may be also "dear/darling" as an address to your husband}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear guest, on your request, we have prepared \Nanother table for your own rendezvous. {I hope he means this by "in the meantime, separate seat ..." and they just assumed, the two got to the same table by mistake, I would assume that's what he called a waiter for in previous scene}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.27,0:12:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.85,0:12:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I'd like to stay here for a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.17,0:12:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At least until I get a chance to take a quick glance \Nat the world's happiest woman today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.75,0:12:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you be talking about the woman over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.07,0:12:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.68,0:12:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You two know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.71,0:12:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it was you all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. \NWhy would Editor go to the trouble of writing a letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter didn't actually come from Frau Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you playing innocent now? \NWhat's the point after coming this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.88,0:13:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I should be asking! \NMaking me come all the way to here... {/calling me to a place like this}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.88,0:13:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I would never...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Save your breath! {/I know already}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.77,0:13:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you did it to make me listen \Nto this man's vaunting about his love. {boastful talk about one's love life; speaking fondly about one's sweetheart; going on about one's love affairs}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Vaunting about love?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.98,0:13:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one playing innocent here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.59,0:13:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.84,0:13:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're at it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.63,0:13:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Habersetzer...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? It appears, this place is swarming \Nwith the invitees of yours. {/on this side too, your buddy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.27,0:13:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my, isn't that Herr Palfy himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.72,0:13:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,May I express my admiration for your concert last night? {lit: was actually spectacular}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That was some of the finest cacophony I've ever heard! {/that's exactly what they call second-class music}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.74,0:14:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's clear to me. From all sides, \NI'm besieged by the pawns in your scheme. {/this and that - everyone acts acccording to your plan}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.74,0:14:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you invited me here - intending to make fun of, \Nto affront in the most insulting manner!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.69,0:14:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough! {majorly guess, but jikken may be "seeing with one's own eyes; witnessing" but I already included this in previous line so w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.56,0:14:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why... {now I'm convinced she uses anata as "my husband" but she technically isn't and it's emotionally neutral in japanese, but in english we only have affectionate "darling/honey"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.23,0:14:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear, do they really call him \NPalfy, the great musician?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.83,0:14:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, so far, I'm utterly disappointed with him. {disappointment; despair}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be joking...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.27,0:14:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,With a head as dense as yours, \Nappreciating his music is unachievable even in a lifetime! {/someone like you will never have patience to understand his music}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an unforeseen trouble, \Nthat made his concert go wrack and ruin! {spoiled; spoilt; ruined; wasted (chance, etc.); messed up; destroyed; (coming to) nothing​}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,His music is only born out of genuine kindness! {/overflowing with}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody but me is destined to ever truly understand it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:14:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"Nobody but me?" {I hope he is just repeating what she said and not adding "it's only me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.82,0:15:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.23,0:15:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No clue what's this all about, \Nbut our lunch is ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.36,0:15:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll file a complaint! {/is spoiled; spoilt; ruined; wasted (chance, etc.); messed up; destroyed; (coming to) nothing​!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.90,0:15:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.77,0:15:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom's manuscript!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.02,0:16:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"Even though his last concert \Nhad ended in such a grand-scale fiasco,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.93,0:16:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the inhabitants of the Earth \Nwill soon let it fade into oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.67,0:16:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's still Herr Ludwig Palfy \Nwho they call the best musician of our time."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.34,0:16:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have said too much earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.65,0:16:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I know perfectly well, you're not the kind of woman \Nwho'd ever be so gravely vindictive. {mean; contemptible; despicable; dirty; foul; cowardly; base}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:17:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't seem like a half-bad guy either, \Nyour new man. {/it seems everything is going smoothly for you and ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, you're a really good match.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.95,0:17:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Fare thee well. {/be happy}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.26,0:17:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To you as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.60,0:17:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"Whenever you listen to it, \Nhis music is capable of evoking
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.67,0:17:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this ever-changing love, \Nthat usually just lies dormant in our chests."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.27,0:17:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.44,0:17:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even to this day, mom still remembers dad \Nwith such warm feelings! {respect; esteem; reverence; honour; honor}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.90,0:17:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, too, probably only got so worked up \Nbecause jealousy was searing him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This means, they can start getting along again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.84,0:17:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, it's been some while\Nsince the last time we swapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.42,0:18:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd really like to stay with dad for a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.95,0:18:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I also feel that there's a hundred and one thing \NI still need to discuss with mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.20,0:18:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it's saddening \Nthat Munich and Vienna are so far apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll definitely meet again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.14,0:18:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.89,0:18:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The train is leaving soon. \NHurry up to join dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.56,0:18:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Please look after mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll write you a letter soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.58,0:19:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"It'll be quite a while \Nbefore I get to see dad and Lotte again" -
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.47,0:19:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in Luise's chest, the feeling of loneliness \Nwas on the rise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Lotte \Nwas experiencing the exact same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, however, the two part, \Nfirmly resolved to set their sights on an even higher peak. {not sure what he means: it's the parting towards a new decision/commitment}
Comment: 0,0:20:20.37,0:20:20.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:29.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.84,0:20:33.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.30,0:20:37.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:39.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.15,0:20:51.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.57,0:20:55.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.33,0:20:58.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.87,0:21:02.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.71,0:21:05.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:08.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.84,0:21:13.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.39,0:21:17.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.09,0:21:22.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:26.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.15,0:21:29.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.78,0:21:32.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:37.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.37,0:21:40.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.37,0:21:44.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.45,0:21:46.45,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.88,0:21:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I was anxious to know \Nhow dad actually feels about mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to atelier to check!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.16,0:21:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.36,0:21:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The glass frame that mom's photo was stored in, was now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.36,0:21:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me it was broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.73,0:22:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, could it be that dad
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.10,0:22:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,had come to hate mom now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.90,0:22:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're overthinking again! Cheer up, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.97,0:22:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.17,0:22:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad Doesn't Know Himself!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.97,0:22:15.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 19 \NWe Can't Understand Dad!? {really no clue what they mean, but is this title doesn't fit will replace later}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.91,0:22:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Look forward to it!
